quran[18]{c,v,t}:
  49,1,"O believers! Do not proceed Ћєin any matterЋЇ before Ћєa decree fromЋЇ Allah and His Messenger. And fear Allah. Surely Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  49,2,"O believers! Do not raise your voices above the voice of the Prophet, nor speak loudly to him as you do to one another,¬†or your deeds will become void while you are unaware"
  49,3,"Indeed, those who lower their voices in the presence of AllahвАЩs Messenger are the ones whose hearts Allah has refined for righteousness. They will have forgiveness and a great reward"
  49,4,"Indeed, most of those who call out to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ from outside ЋєyourЋЇ private quarters have no understanding Ћєof mannersЋЇ"
  49,5,"Had they been patient until you could come out to them, it would have certainly been better for them. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  49,6,"O believers, if an evildoer brings you any news, verify ЋєitЋЇ so you do not harm people unknowingly, becoming regretful for what you have done"
  49,7,"And keep in mind that AllahвАЩs Messenger is ЋєstillЋЇ in your midst. If he were to yield to you in many matters, you would surely suffer Ћєthe consequencesЋЇ.¬†But Allah has endeared faith to you, making it appealing in your hearts. And He has made disbelief, rebelliousness, and disobedience detestable to you. Those are the ones rightly guided"
  49,8,"ЋєThis isЋЇ a bounty and a blessing from Allah. And Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  49,9,"And if two groups of believers fight each other, then make peace between them. But if one of them transgresses against the other, then fight against the transgressing group until they Ћєare willing toЋЇ submit to the rule of Allah. If they do so, then make peace between both ЋєgroupsЋЇ in all fairness and act justly. Surely Allah loves those who uphold justice"
  49,10,"The believers are but one brotherhood, so make peace between your brothers. And be mindful of Allah so you may be shown mercy"
  49,11,"O believers! Do not let some ЋєmenЋЇ ridicule others, they may be better than them, nor let ЋєsomeЋЇ women ridicule other women, they may be better than them. Do not defame one another, nor call each other by offensive nicknames. How evil it is to act rebelliously after having faith! And whoever does not repent, it is they who are the ЋєtrueЋЇ wrongdoers"
  49,12,"O believers! Avoid many suspicions, ЋєforЋЇ indeed, some suspicions are sinful. And do not spy, nor backbite one another. Would any of you like to eat the flesh of their dead brother? You would despise that!¬†And fear Allah. Surely Allah is ЋєtheЋЇ Accepter of Repentance, Most Merciful"
  49,13,"O humanity! Indeed, We created you from a male and a female, and made you into peoples and tribes so that you may Ћєget toЋЇ know one another. Surely the most noble of you in the sight of Allah is the most righteous among you. Allah is truly All-Knowing, All-Aware"
  49,14,"ЋєSome ofЋЇ the nomadic Arabs say, вАЬWe believe.вАЭ Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬYou have not believed. But say, вАШWe have submitted,вАЩ for faith has not yet entered your hearts.¬†But if you obey Allah and His Messenger ЋєwholeheartedlyЋЇ, He will not discount anything from Ћєthe reward ofЋЇ your deeds. Allah is truly All-Forgiving, Most Merciful.вАЭ"
  49,15,The ЋєtrueЋЇ believers are only those who believe in Allah and His MessengerвАФnever doubtingвАФand strive with their wealth and their lives in the cause of Allah. They are the ones true in faith
  49,16,"Say, вАЬDo you inform Allah of your faith, when Allah ЋєalreadyЋЇ knows whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth? And Allah has ЋєperfectЋЇ knowledge of all things.вАЭ"
  49,17,"They regard their acceptance of Islam as a favour to you. Tell Ћєthem, O ProphetЋЇ, вАЬDo not regard your Islam as a favour to me. Rather, it is Allah Who has done you a favour by guiding you to the faith, if ЋєindeedЋЇ you are faithful"
  49,18,Surely Allah knows the unseen of the heavens and earth. And Allah is All-Seeing of what you do.вАЭ